# Shared Types Package – @repo/types

The `packages/types` package is the **single source of truth** for all data shapes. Both the mobile app and web app import from `@repo/types`.

## Pattern: Zod Schema → Inferred TypeScript Type

Always define schemas first, then infer types. Never write standalone TypeScript interfaces that duplicate Zod schemas.

```typescript
// packages/types/src/wallet.ts
import { z } from 'zod';

export const walletTypeSchema = z.enum([
  'bank', 'cash', 'credit', 'debit', 'ewallet', 'investment', 'other',
]);

// Full entity schema (what the DB returns)
export const walletSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  userId: z.string().uuid(),
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  type: walletTypeSchema,
  currency: z.string().length(3),
  initialBalance: z.number(),
  color: z.string().regex(/^#[0-9A-Fa-f]{6}$/),
  icon: z.string(),
  isActive: z.boolean(),
  displayOrder: z.number(),
  createdAt: z.string().datetime(),
  updatedAt: z.string().datetime(),
});

// Request schema (subset — what clients send)
export const createWalletSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  type: walletTypeSchema,
  currency: z.string().length(3).default('USD'),
  initialBalance: z.number().default(0),
  color: z.string().regex(/^#[0-9A-Fa-f]{6}$/),
  icon: z.string(),
});

export const updateWalletSchema = createWalletSchema.partial();

// Infer TypeScript types from Zod
export type Wallet = z.infer<typeof walletSchema>;
export type CreateWallet = z.infer<typeof createWalletSchema>;
export type UpdateWallet = z.infer<typeof updateWalletSchema>;

// API response wrapper types
export type WalletResponse = { wallet: Wallet };
export type WalletListResponse = { wallets: Wallet[] };
```

## File Structure

```
packages/types/src/
├── index.ts        - Re-export everything
├── api.ts          - ApiError, Pagination, ListResponse<T>
├── wallet.ts
├── transaction.ts  - includes transactionListParamsSchema
├── category.ts
├── tag.ts
├── user.ts
├── analytics.ts    - Dashboard overview response types
└── sync.ts         - SyncPushRequest, SyncPushResponse, SyncPullResponse
```

Always re-export from `index.ts` after adding a new file.

## Common API Types (api.ts)

```typescript
export type ApiError = { error: string; details?: unknown };

export type Pagination = {
  page: number;
  limit: number;
  total: number;
  totalPages: number;
};

export type ListResponse<T> = {
  data: T[];
  pagination: Pagination;
};
```

## Transaction Schema Example (with refinements)

```typescript
export const createTransactionSchema = z.object({
  walletId: z.string().uuid(),
  amount: z.number().positive(),
  type: z.enum(['income', 'expense', 'transfer']),
  categoryId: z.string().uuid().optional(),
  transferToWalletId: z.string().uuid().optional(),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
  transactionDate: z.string().datetime().optional(),
  tagIds: z.array(z.string().uuid()).optional(),
}).refine(
  (data) => data.type !== 'transfer' || !!data.transferToWalletId,
  { message: 'Transfer must specify a target wallet' }
);
```

## Usage Rules

- ✅ Import Zod schemas on both client and server for runtime validation
- ✅ Import inferred types for TypeScript compile-time safety
- ✅ Use `.parse()` to validate — throws `ZodError` on invalid input
- ✅ Use `.safeParse()` when you want to handle errors without try/catch
- ❌ Never manually cast API responses without parsing (use the schema)
- ❌ Never duplicate schema definitions across apps
